Dear Hiring Team, 

It is with great pleasure that I submit my candidacy for the *Ambient Agents Engineer* with *Commure*. I bring over three years of professional experience in building scalable Node.js/Express backends, RAG systems, and AI agent orchestration, along with a strong academic foundation as a Master of Science in Computer Science graduate from Pace University, NY.

Through my experience across engineering roles, I have built and delivered production-grade systems that directly reflect *the technical depth this position demands in architecting multi-agent orchestration systems and building scalable Node.js backends*. As a Software Engineer at Sperse, I architected a concurrent multi-agent orchestration system using LangChain and LangGraph to enable scalable tool execution across enterprise workflows. I also developed an MCP interaction layer that translates natural-language intents into safe, validated tool calls across 1,000+ endpoints—ensuring *Security by Design* while reducing end-to-end latency by 60% through prompt routing and concurrency optimizations. Prior to Sperse, at Qualitest, I built an internal support *Ambient Agent* using RAG and a PostgreSQL vector store, which reduced ticket resolution times by 20%. I also designed a cloud-agnostic Storage Service using Node.js and developed complex backend workflows using Kafka and AWS Step Functions to handle high-volume data imports—addressing *the kind of systems-level thinking and operational stability focus this role demands at Commure*. These roles have prepared me to *contribute meaningfully to the team's core engineering responsibilities by designing, developing, and deploying complex AI-powered features that enhance healthcare workflows*.

My academic research and leadership experience have given me a rigorous foundation in model lifecycle management and technical mentorship—skills that translate directly into *the action-biased "Day 1" culture and commitment to extreme ownership this team values*. As an AI Researcher at the Pace Artificial Intelligence Lab, I managed the full ML lifecycle for generative models using PyTorch and CUDA, optimizing inference with vLLM for high-performance deployment. Beyond individual contributions, I led technical workshops on building AI Agents with LangChain and LangGraph for 50+ students. This experience required me to break down complex technical concepts and promote best practices—directly mirroring *the mentorship and knowledge-sharing responsibilities central to this role*. I am eager to bring this blend of technical rigor and collaborative spirit to *Commure and its mission to reimagine care delivery*.

I have always been passionate about *Speed Above All Else and Extreme Ownership* and envision myself contributing my talent to the furthering of *creating the "operating system for healthcare" and simplifying the industry for providers and patients*. I would love to discuss my interest in this position with your team and can be reached at #ph or #eml. Thank you for your time and consideration, I look forward to connecting!

